FAQ

Find Your Answers

How secure is Crypture's platform?

Crypture prioritizes security with advanced encryption technology and strict security protocols to safeguard your digital assets. Our platform undergoes regular security audits to maintain the highest standards of protection.

What cryptocurrencies does support?

Crypture supports a variety of cryptocurrencies, including Bitcoin (BTC), Ethereum (ETH), Litecoin (LTC), and more. For a complete list of supported cryptocurrencies, please refer to our website or contact customer support.

How do I activate my Crypture card?

To activate your Crypture card, follow the simple instructions provided in your welcome package or through the Crypture mobile app. You'll need to link your card to your Crypture account and verify your identity for security purposes.

Can I use Crypture for online purchases?

Crypture can be used for online purchases wherever cryptocurrencies are accepted. Simply enter your Crypture card details at checkout to complete the transaction securely.

Can I use Crypture internationally?

Yes, Crypture is designed for global use. You can use your Crypture card for transactions worldwide, making it convenient for travel and international business.

What are Crypture's transaction limits?

Crypture offers customizable transaction limits based on your chosen plan. Standard plans typically have lower transaction limits compared to premium plans, which may offer higher limits and additional benefits.
